

FOR INSERTING WEEK HEADERS:
Be sure to uncheck the ". matches newline" checkbox

Search:
	(Monday, )(January|February|March|April|May|June|July|August|September|October|November|December)( [0-9]+)(, [0-9]+)\n((.+\n){5})(^Sunday, )(January|February|March|April|May|June|July|August|September|October|November|December)( [0-9]+, 202[0-9])
Replace:
	\n\n\2\3 - \8\9\n\n\1\2\3\4\n\5\7\8\9




By using an optional limited character class in the Sunday date that only includes the single digits 1-7 [1-7], that can be used to identify the times the month name should be included. Otherwise, if the date is a single digit of 8 or 9, or is a double digit, [8-31], the first month name can be used.


Put a blank line between each day:
Search:
	(.+day)
Replace:
	\n\1


Inserting tasks into each day:

First, insert the priority subheaders under each day.
Search pattern:
	^(.+day.+2025)\n
	^(.+day.+2026)\n
Replace pattern:
	\1\nTop Priorities\nThings that MUST get done:\nONGOING Things to do:\nThings that SHOULD get done:\nThings I'd LIKE to get done:\nOTHER things to do:\n




Sunday
Search:
	(Sunday.+\n)(.+\n)(.+MUST get done:\n)
Replace:
	\1\2\3I am stronger than anything that comes at me\nTake morning drugs\n8 a.m.: Choir rehearsal\n8:30 a.m.: Worship @ St. John's\nChoir anthem:\n10:45 a.m.: Worship @ St. John's\nDuolingo\nGive Prozac to Tristan\nTake evening drugs\n

